OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F305A1766897199
OL,3,C'Dubious' if all-island court would
OL,4,Cconvict more fugitives ` Irish AG in
OL,5,C1982
OL,7,F"The attorney general was of the
OL,8,Fopinion that the proposal considered
OL,9,Fin this regard was a cumbersome
OL,10,Farrangement, the merits of which in
OL,11,Fterms of securing more convictions of
OL,12,Ffugitive offenders were, in his view,
OL,13,Frather dubious.
OL,15,F"There were particular difficulties as
OL,16,Fregards the question of whether a
OL,17,Fright of appeal would lie."
OL,26,@oD@AOUwD@AOUyD@[O]
