OL,7,FThe note from that meeting stated that
OL,8,Ftalks had begun between the British
OL,9,Fand Irish attorneys general and since
OL,10,Fthen, "there was pressure from the
OL,11,FBritish side for us to advance our
OL,12,Fposition on extradition and joint
OL,13,Fquestioning".
OL,15,FIt also noted that there was "no
OL,16,Fprospect" of the British agreeing to a
OL,17,Fjoint court without movement on joint
OL,18,Fquestioning or extradition.
OL,26,@rD@GOUuD@LO]wD@^OUxD@IO]
