OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F305A1766897199
OL,3,C'Dubious' if all-island court would
OL,4,Cconvict more fugitives ` Irish AG in
OL,5,C1982
OL,7,F"It was questioned as to whether such
OL,8,Fa formula could work in practice and
OL,9,Ffurther clarification of the position
OL,10,Fwas felt to be necessary."
OL,12,FIt also noted that while there was
OL,13,Funiformity of legislation, rules of
OL,14,Fevidence differed which was relevant
OL,15,Fto admissions of guilt and could be an
OL,16,F"enormous obstacle".
OL,18,F"It was agreed that the term 'all-
OL,19,Fisland court' was politically
OL,20,Fsensitive and that a more appropriate
OL,21,Ftitle might be 'joint court'."
